            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>pulled pork joint </strong>to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong>,<strong> </strong>draining away <strong>half </strong>of the juices</p><p>Sprinkle over the <strong>ground cumin</strong> and <strong>smoked paprika</strong> with 2/3 of the <strong>cider vinegar</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>honey</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and rub it into the pork, using the back of a spoon</p><p>Cover with <strong>tin foil</strong> and put the dish in the oven for 25 min, removing the foil for the final 5 min</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1650990694547-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
